The paper deals with the transmission of a Gaussian source over a Gaussian multiple-access channel, which is a classic problem in information theory and communication engineering. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of statistical techniques to analyze the performance of the system, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of optimizing the distortion of the transmitted signal, which is a key issue in networked systems, suggesting that it could also be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
